{"cursor":"2736","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{ infobox nobility\n| name = Conrad I of Burgundy image = caption = father = Rudolph II of Burgundy\n| mother = Bertha of Swabia spouse = Matilda of France birth_date = issue =\n| Bertha Matilda Rudolph\n*Gerberga\n| death_date = death_place =\n}} 'Conrad the Peaceful' ( â 19 October 993) was the king of Burgundy from 937\nuntil his death. He was the son of King Rudolph II, the first king of a united\nBurgundy and Queen Bertha of Swabia. Conrad is sometimes numbered 'Conrad I' as\nking of Burgundy and as 'Conrad III of Provence', since he inherited Provence in\n948. Morby, John E. The Wordsworth Handbook of Kings & Queens, 1989.\n\nHis reign was peaceful (hence his byname) and he was popular with his subjects.\nThe only war in which he got involved was a simultaneous invasion of Saracens\nand Magyars in which he played them off against each other. He then routed them\nin combat.\n\nHe married Matilda, daughter of Louis IV of France and Gerberga of Saxony. {{cite book |last=Reuter |first=Timothy |title=The New Cambridge\nMedieval History: c. 900-c. 1024 |publisher=Cambridge University Press\n|location= |year=2000 |isbn=0-521-36447-7 |accessdate=2011-01-31}} They\nhad at least four children: *Bertha (967 â 16 January 1016), married Odo I,\nCount of Blois, and then Robert II of France *Matilda (born 969), possibly\nmarried Robert, Count of Geneva *Rudolph (971 â 6 September 1032) *Gerberga\n(born 965), married Herman II, Duke of Swabia\n\nHe was secondly married to Adelaide of Bellay. They were parents to at least one\ndaughter, Gisela.\n","linknr":125,"url":"Conrad_of_Burgundy","recorded":1374543666,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Conrad_I_of_Burgundy&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Conrad_I_of_Burgundy&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special